fields.descriptive_line: Toy bunker and trench set, with eight British infantry soldiers and two explosions, painted wood, cardboard and wire, and hand-painted composite material (Elastolin), Germany, ca.1920s.

fields.physical_description:
Toy  bunker set, with one bunker and two trench segments in painted wood and cardboard, eight British infantry soldiers in varying poses and two explosions, made of Elastolin and painted.
[model explosion] Moulded composite explosion, hand-painted, with a roughly conical, honeycombed base, painted dark green, coming from which are yellow and red flames, linear in form, culminating in black smoke. Silver pieces of shrapnel are also present.
[model explosion] Moulded plastic explosion, hand-painted, with a circular dark brown base moulded to resemble earth, red and yellow flames shooting out from it, and a cloud of light grey smoke. Small pieces of black rock or shrapnel are also represented.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry) on an oval base, holding a rifle running. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with 'tommy' helmet, light-brown belt with black, brown and grey attachments, and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The rifle is painted brown with a silver muzzle and details, the base dark green.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry), crawling on his front holding a stick grenade in his right hand. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with five silver buttons on front of tunic, and is also wearing a khaki green 'tommy' helmet, light-brown belt and black and brown attachements, and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The stick grenade  has a brown shaft and silver tip.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry) on an oval base, holding a rifle with arms outstretched as if just shot. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with 'tommy' helmet, light-brown belt with black and brown attachments, and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The rifle is painted brown with a silver muzzle, the base dark green.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry) on base, right arm outstretched firing a pistol. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with 'tommy' helmet, light-brown and silver belt, and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The pistol is painted black with a silver muzzle. The base is painted dark green.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (American infantry?), lying on his front firing a mounted machine gun. The figure is wearing a uniform of dark khaki green with 'tommy' helmet, light-green belt and attachments, and brown boots. A black shield is painted on each shoulder, containing a red number 1, with a red strip across the top containing three white dots.  The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The machine gun is painted tan, with a black muzzle and silver ribbon of ammunition down each side.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry), lying on his front firing a rifle. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with six silver buttons on front of tunic, and is also wearing a khaki green 'tommy' helmet, light-brown belt with gold buckle and black and brown attachements and silver canteen. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The rifle is painted brown and silver.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry), lying on his front firing a rifle. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with six silver buttons on front of tunic, and is also wearing a khaki green 'tommy' helmet, light-brown belt with gold buckle and black and brown attachements, a grey, silver and brown rucksack and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The rifle is painted brown and silver.
[toy soldier] Hand-painted Elastolin toy soldier (British infantry), lying on his front firing a rifle. The figure is wearing a uniform of khaki green with six silver buttons on front of tunic, and is also wearing a khaki green 'tommy' helmet, brown belt with black and brown attachements, a khaki and brown rucksack and brown boots. The face and hands are painted flesh pink, with facial details picked out in black and red. The rifle is painted brown and silver.
[toy trench] Wood and cardboard trench section, glued and nailed onto rectangular painted wooden base.With two wave-shaped walls each held in place by five poles. The external walls are roughly 'textured' and painted brown with light green and orange mottling. The internal walls and base is painted dark brown. The underside of base has two strips of wood pinned across each end.
[toy trench] Wood and cardboard trench section, glued and nailed onto rectangular painted wooden base.With wave-shaped interior walls held in place by five poles, and with a vertical rear external wall and curved front external wall, the latter with wire stretched between seven poles embedded into it. The external walls are roughly 'textured' and painted brown with light green and orange mottling. The internal walls and base is painted dark brown. The underside of base has two strips of wood pinned across each end.
[toy bunker] Wood and cardboard bunker complex, glued and nailed onto rectangular painted wooden base. The bunker has two windowless 'rooms', one square, one narrow, separated by a flight of steps to their roofs with a roughly crenalated front wall. At either side of the rooms a low wall extends to the edge of the base and a short pole. The external walls are roughly 'textured' and painted light green, with brown mottling. To the rear are two low walls supported by poles, also textured and painted, and a wooden telegraph pole.

fields.public_access_description: This bunker set includes eight soldiers in various poses in British infantry uniform, as well as two model explosions. This would not have been sold as a complete set, and individual parts would have been purchased separately. The majority of the set was manufactured by O & M Hausser, a well-known German company, although at least one of the explosions was produced by a rival company, Lineol, also based in Germany. The bunker and trench segments are made from wood and cardboard, and the soldiers and explosions from a composite material (for which Hausser's used the tradename Elastolin), produced from mixing sawdust, glue, casein and kaolin. This mixture was placed into a mould around a wire armature, then gently heated and dried before being hand-painted. The set reflects the trend amongst toy soldier manufacturers to mirror the real world in terms of new military equipment and modes of warfare.
fields.history_note: This set, consisting of bunker, trench sections and figures was not sold as a complete set. The individual parts have therefore been purchased separately and, possibly, collected together over time. The bunker, trench sections and the majority of the soldiers were manufactured in the 1920s by the well-known German manufacturer O & M Hausser, who used the Elastolin trademark for their composite figures. At least one of the explosions, and possibly several soldiers, were produced by Lineol, a rival company to Hausser, again based in Germany, it is assumed at a similar period.
fields.historical_context_note: These soldiers would have been played with by children. They reflect the trend amongst toy soldier manufacturers to mirror the real world in terms of new armies, regiments, changes in uniform and equipment and methods of warfare, and were manufactured to be an accurate representation of the, at the time, recently ended First World War.
